1
00:00:06,758 --> 00:00:09,084
Thailand was such a dream.

2
00:00:09,084 --> 00:00:11,084
It was awesome.

3
00:00:12,084 --> 00:00:14,511
Let's go together next time.

4
00:00:14,511 --> 00:00:16,371
Sounds great.

5
00:00:16,371 --> 00:00:18,113
Pinky promise?

6
00:00:22,044 --> 00:00:23,478
But first,

7
00:00:23,478 --> 00:00:26,600
let's survive today's presentation.

8
00:00:28,584 --> 00:00:30,354
Oh, right.

9
00:00:32,098 --> 00:00:33,799
You ready?

10
00:00:35,231 --> 00:00:36,718
Yeah.

11
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:42,294
Let's go.

12
00:00:45,738 --> 00:00:47,293
Let's go.

13
00:00:49,284 --> 00:00:53,080
Now, shall we start with Team 5's presentation?

14
00:00:54,111 --> 00:00:55,544
Two, three...

15
00:00:55,544 --> 00:00:57,544
- Hello.
- Hello.

16
00:00:59,184 --> 00:01:01,244
Our team, unlike the others,

17
00:01:01,244 --> 00:01:04,648
is a combination of Korean and Thai.

18
00:01:04,648 --> 00:01:07,615
At first,
we couldn't understand each other at all.

19
00:01:07,615 --> 00:01:10,598
It was hard to say the least.

20
00:01:10,598 --> 00:01:12,671
As we were figuring out what to do,

21
00:01:12,671 --> 00:01:14,882
we decided to take
our own experience into account...

22
00:01:14,882 --> 00:01:19,591
and to focus on international marriage
between Korea and Thailand.

23
00:01:20,591 --> 00:01:22,771
We'll now present

24
00:01:22,771 --> 00:01:24,767
how we came to understand our differences

25
00:01:24,767 --> 00:01:27,689
and made the decision to marry.

26
00:01:30,678 --> 00:01:33,491
That American producer seems pretty talented.

27
00:01:33,491 --> 00:01:36,418
- We might reach America after all.
- Could we go there?

28
00:01:36,418 --> 00:01:37,804
Why not?

29
00:01:37,804 --> 00:01:39,804
Let's do it.

30
00:02:15,344 --> 00:02:17,554
[Next Stage Final Scores]

31
00:02:20,265 --> 00:02:22,284
Director Park. Hurry up.

32
00:02:22,284 --> 00:02:23,584
Yes, sir.

33
00:02:23,584 --> 00:02:25,584
Interesting.

34
00:02:29,324 --> 00:02:31,324
Oh, Hyun Jae.

35
00:02:32,697 --> 00:02:34,278
Good evening, sir.

36
00:02:34,278 --> 00:02:36,498
You're here early.

37
00:02:36,498 --> 00:02:38,995
- Have a seat.
- Hello, sir.

38
00:02:44,524 --> 00:02:48,991
I noticed that you and Soo An
weren't on the best of terms.

39
00:02:48,991 --> 00:02:51,731
Did you two have a lovers' quarrel?

40
00:02:51,731 --> 00:02:53,511
No, sir.

41
00:02:53,511 --> 00:02:55,538
I've straightened myself out since then.

42
00:02:55,538 --> 00:02:57,271
Really?

43
00:02:57,271 --> 00:02:59,464
Good thinking, Hyun Jae.

44
00:02:59,464 --> 00:03:02,037
That's what's best for Soo An as well.

45
00:03:02,037 --> 00:03:03,128
Think of Jae Min.

46
00:03:03,128 --> 00:03:04,838
That's what happens when there's a scandal.

47
00:03:04,838 --> 00:03:06,864
With an idol, no less!

48
00:03:06,864 --> 00:03:08,571
I'll keep that in mind, sir.

49
00:03:08,571 --> 00:03:11,464
Hyun Jae, we're in the same boat.

50
00:03:11,464 --> 00:03:15,603
If either of us screws up
and sinks this boat, we both drown.

51
00:03:15,603 --> 00:03:17,381
If it works out, we both survive.

52
00:03:17,381 --> 00:03:19,464
Got it?

53
00:03:19,464 --> 00:03:21,717
Yes, sir, I do.

54
00:03:22,624 --> 00:03:26,344
You even had to rig the chart for me.

55
00:03:27,004 --> 00:03:28,937
[All recordings]
I was so clueless back then.

56
00:03:28,937 --> 00:03:30,284
I'm sorry, sir.

57
00:03:30,284 --> 00:03:32,931
Well, you know now. That's good enough.

58
00:03:32,931 --> 00:03:36,691
Don't worry about PD Lee.
He only cares about money.

59
00:03:37,790 --> 00:03:41,857
Director Park told me
that you've been working hard lately.

60
00:03:41,857 --> 00:03:43,857
He really is.

61
00:03:44,738 --> 00:03:46,531
Of course, as I should.

62
00:03:46,531 --> 00:03:48,630
In fact, I'm going to work myself to death.

63
00:03:51,191 --> 00:03:52,918
Good.

64
00:04:20,524 --> 00:04:22,671
That kind of toughness...

65
00:04:22,671 --> 00:04:25,729
is the only way you can survive in this field.

66
00:04:27,011 --> 00:04:29,258
I don't cheap out on my people.

67
00:04:29,258 --> 00:04:30,988
And I mean it.

68
00:04:37,486 --> 00:04:39,571
And lastly,

69
00:04:40,704 --> 00:04:43,158
Soo An, in this incident...

70
00:04:43,158 --> 00:04:45,229
is the biggest victim.

71
00:04:47,071 --> 00:04:49,598
Which is why I ask...

72
00:04:49,598 --> 00:04:52,401
another opportunity be given to him.

73
00:04:54,677 --> 00:04:57,423
All the punishment for this...

74
00:04:58,704 --> 00:05:00,459
should be directed to me.

75
00:05:00,459 --> 00:05:02,096
That is all.

76
00:05:12,084 --> 00:05:14,571
Kim Hyun Jae, you bastard.

77
00:05:16,178 --> 00:05:19,747
Why are you trying to take full responsibility?

78
00:05:23,058 --> 00:05:26,360
Did you seriously think
I'd be happy about this?

79
00:05:26,951 --> 00:05:28,951
I swear, I will hate you.

80
00:05:29,904 --> 00:05:32,726
I'll hate you my whole life.

81
00:05:44,398 --> 00:05:49,140
[Idol Survival Program Officials Prosecuted
CEO and officials accused of bribery]

82
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:54,851
[Kim Hyun Jae, Ex-member of Wakers,
Disappears After Exposing the Truth]

83
00:05:54,851 --> 00:05:59,039
[One year later]

84
00:06:01,671 --> 00:06:03,964
Cut. Good job, everyone.

85
00:06:03,964 --> 00:06:05,964
Let's wrap this up.

86
00:06:06,671 --> 00:06:08,877
Good work!

87
00:06:11,051 --> 00:06:12,738
Tired?

88
00:06:16,118 --> 00:06:17,586
I'm fine.

89
00:06:17,586 --> 00:06:19,457
You must be more tired than I am.

90
00:06:19,457 --> 00:06:22,591
I'm actually thrilled to see you on stage.

91
00:06:22,591 --> 00:06:24,810
Considering what Unicorn did to you...

92
00:06:25,771 --> 00:06:27,607
This is what you call a blessing in disguise.

93
00:06:27,607 --> 00:06:30,051
Thanks to what happened to PNJS,
you can move on to greener pastures.

94
00:06:30,051 --> 00:06:33,103
You'll receive better care,
and a better road to your debut.

95
00:06:33,711 --> 00:06:35,937
Thank you.

96
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:37,408
For...

97
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:40,769
having my back even at my lowest.

98
00:06:56,451 --> 00:06:58,778
Hyun Jae.

99
00:06:58,778 --> 00:07:01,385
Where on earth are you?

100
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:09,511
I hated that you disappeared at first...

101
00:07:10,664 --> 00:07:13,116
but now I just feel so sorry.

102
00:07:13,976 --> 00:07:16,218
I've been thinking...

103
00:07:16,964 --> 00:07:19,992
and realized that I know nothing about you.

104
00:07:21,724 --> 00:07:24,117
So, after you left...

105
00:07:24,831 --> 00:07:26,917
Bit by bit...

106
00:07:28,184 --> 00:07:30,564
I've been figuring you out.

107
00:07:46,124 --> 00:07:47,907
[Kim Hyun Jae's fan account]
[Waiting for his return!]

108
00:07:52,545 --> 00:07:57,085
[cafe-class liked your post]

109
00:08:12,270 --> 00:08:13,982
Are you ready?

110
00:08:24,150 --> 00:08:26,863
Hello, everyone. Hello.

111
00:08:29,236 --> 00:08:30,556
Thank you for waiting for me.

112
00:08:30,556 --> 00:08:33,316
I hope I can make it up to you today.

113
00:08:33,316 --> 00:08:35,036
Before we start, however...

114
00:08:35,036 --> 00:08:37,836
I'm not here alone.

115
00:08:37,836 --> 00:08:39,575
This person gave me so much strength.

116
00:08:39,575 --> 00:08:41,679
Strength to return to you guys.

117
00:08:45,396 --> 00:08:48,683
Hello, my name is Shin Jae Min.

118
00:08:48,683 --> 00:08:50,856
I'm from Korea.

119
00:08:50,856 --> 00:08:53,343
I'm currently learning Thai.

120
00:08:53,343 --> 00:08:55,637
So bear with me.

121
00:09:00,496 --> 00:09:01,843
Well, then.

122
00:09:01,843 --> 00:09:03,843
Shall we?

123
00:09:10,343 --> 00:09:12,075
You know what?

124
00:09:12,850 --> 00:09:15,175
My wish came true.

125
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:18,540
Mine, too.

126
00:09:20,396 --> 00:09:24,423
We've fought due to differences
in our background and culture.

127
00:09:24,423 --> 00:09:28,035
But, through those experiences,
we learned about each other,

128
00:09:28,035 --> 00:09:30,423
and grew closer than ever.

129
00:09:30,423 --> 00:09:32,090
As our relationship grew,

130
00:09:32,090 --> 00:09:35,716
we realized that nationality didn't matter.

131
00:09:35,716 --> 00:09:38,016
Because we wanted to know each other,

132
00:09:38,016 --> 00:09:40,040
we would study each other's languages,

133
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:43,630
or learn about each other's country.

134
00:09:43,630 --> 00:09:47,445
Love has changed so much about us.

135
00:09:47,445 --> 00:09:50,109
We grew mature through those times.

136
00:09:50,109 --> 00:09:53,210
We learned that in marriage,
we share sadness and happiness.

137
00:09:53,210 --> 00:09:55,216
We have to marry someone
whom we love so dearly,

138
00:09:55,216 --> 00:09:58,730
so that we can stand strong
against any hardship thrown at us.

139
00:09:58,730 --> 00:10:02,630
We also learned that two different people,
from different countries,

140
00:10:02,630 --> 00:10:07,850
can become family through marriage.

141
00:10:07,850 --> 00:10:10,496
In conclusion...

142
00:10:10,496 --> 00:10:14,683
marriage, which allows two people
in love to spend their whole lives together...

143
00:10:14,683 --> 00:10:18,451
is the greatest blessing
that one could possibly choose.

144
00:10:18,451 --> 00:10:20,429
This is our humble opinion.

145
00:10:21,096 --> 00:10:24,096
This was Team 5, and we are...

146
00:10:25,396 --> 00:10:26,896
Khun.

147
00:10:26,896 --> 00:10:28,667
And Shin Jae Min. Thank you.

148
00:10:28,667 --> 00:10:30,242
Thank you.

149
00:11:14,310 --> 00:11:16,310
Sorry to keep you waiting.

150
00:11:18,636 --> 00:11:19,861
My apologies.

151
00:11:19,861 --> 00:11:21,348
Just a minute.

152
00:11:21,348 --> 00:11:23,145
What do you need?

153
00:11:23,802 --> 00:11:25,739
An Americano.

154
00:11:27,648 --> 00:11:29,968
It's hot out, isn't it?

155
00:11:29,968 --> 00:11:32,408
This'll cool you down.

156
00:11:34,488 --> 00:11:36,068
Actually, no.

157
00:11:36,915 --> 00:11:38,915
I'll take it hot.

158
00:12:56,985 --> 00:13:01,648
[Thank you for your love for Love Class 3]

